We can now compute the number of shares needed to be sold. This is computed by dividing the sales proceeds by the offer price. This is computed as follows: 

$$\begin{aligned}
{\text{Number of shares }}&=\dfrac{\text{Sales proceed}}{\text{Offer price}}\\[10pt]
&=\dfrac{\text{\$65,806,451.61}}{\text{\$21.00}}\\[10pt]
&={\textbf{3,133,641}}
\end{aligned}$$
